Saute the onion in the oil until the onion is translucent.  Add the hominy, squash, potato and stock.  Bring it to a boil, then simmer until the potato and squash are almost tender.  Add the white beans, corn and green beans and bring back to a boil.  Thicken with either roux or corn starch just enough to give it some body.  Add salt and pepper to taste.
